<paragraph blockId="8.[151,638,453,479]" box="[151,638,453,479]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,638,453,479]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,638,453,479]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
<taxonomicName box="[151,432,453,479]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhomboidea">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,432,453,479]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">Pempheris rhomboidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs 
<taxonomicName box="[472,638,453,479]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[472,638,453,479]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. nesogallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,517,1131]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
The third species reported from the Red Sea by 
<bibRefCitation box="[702,927,517,542]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" refString="Koeda, K., Yoshino, T., Imai, H. &amp; Tachihara, K. (2014). A review of the genus Pempheris (Perciformes, Pempheridae), with description of a new species. Zootaxa, 3793 (3), 301 - 330. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3793.3.1" type="journal article">
Koeda 
<emphasis box="[783,841,517,541]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[858,919,518,542]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[940,1197,517,541]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis box="[940,1197,517,541]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">Pempheris nesogallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,260,551,576]" name="Mauritius" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
by Cuvier in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cuvier" box="[416,751,551,576]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" refString="Cuvier, G. (1831) Des Pempherides. In: Cuvier, G. &amp; Valenciennes, A. (Eds.), Histoire Naturelle des Poissons. Vol. 7. F. G. Levraut, Paris, i - xxix + pp. 1 - 53, pls. 170 - 208. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 7339" type="book chapter" year="1831">
Cuvier &amp; Valenciennes, 
<number box="[692,751,552,576]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="1831.0">1831</number>
</bibRefCitation>
. No 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" box="[804,865,552,576]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" name="Department of Natural Resources, Environment, The Arts and Sport" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">DNA</collectionCode>
sequences are assigned to the species by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="8" pageNumber="385" refString="Koeda, K., Yoshino, T., Imai, H. &amp; Tachihara, K. (2014). A review of the genus Pempheris (Perciformes, Pempheridae), with description of a new species. Zootaxa, 3793 (3), 301 - 330. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3793.3.1" type="journal article">
Koeda 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[194,256,587,611]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Nevertheless, they distinguish it from 
<taxonomicName box="[700,862,587,611]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhomboidea">
<emphasis box="[700,862,587,611]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. rhomboidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(their Red Sea “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1047,1172,587,611]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mangula">
<emphasis box="[1047,1172,587,611]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. mangula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”) arbitrarily by smaller eye size and the lack of stripes. They write, “Of two existing 
<typeStatus box="[868,966,622,646]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1009,1168,621,645]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis box="[1009,1168,621,645]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. nesogallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1242,1354,621,646]" name="Mauritius" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
, one is designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[354,460,655,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">lectotype</typeStatus>
, the other is re-identified as 
<emphasis box="[788,1091,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
<taxonomicName box="[788,918,656,680]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mangula">P. mangula</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName box="[933,1091,656,680]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">P. nesogallica</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is presently known only from the southern Red Sea” (the “only” must refer to ostensible range within the Red Sea itself). Randall D. Mooi examined the two 
<typeStatus box="[359,457,726,750]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[496,653,725,749]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis box="[496,653,725,749]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. nesogallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and found them remarkably similar (as may also be seen in 
<figureCitation box="[1339,1405,725,750]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,2013,2035]" captionTargetBox="[241,1335,1332,1996]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[241,1335,1332,1997]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pempheris nesogallica, BPBM 20144, 117 mm SL, Mauritius (J. E. Randall)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230622/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
Fig. 
<number box="[1391,1405,725,750]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Koeda" box="[151,363,759,784]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" refString="Koeda, K., Yoshino, T., Imai, H. &amp; Tachihara, K. (2014). A review of the genus Pempheris (Perciformes, Pempheridae), with description of a new species. Zootaxa, 3793 (3), 301 - 330. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3793.3.1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Koeda 
<emphasis box="[231,287,760,784]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[302,363,760,784]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)). All the meristic data are the same, or at most one count different.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,517,1131]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
In their key, 
<bibRefCitation box="[343,565,794,819]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" refString="Koeda, K., Yoshino, T., Imai, H. &amp; Tachihara, K. (2014). A review of the genus Pempheris (Perciformes, Pempheridae), with description of a new species. Zootaxa, 3793 (3), 301 - 330. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3793.3.1" type="journal article">
Koeda 
<emphasis box="[425,482,795,819]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[498,557,795,819]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
distinguish 
<taxonomicName box="[704,967,795,819]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhomboidea">
<emphasis box="[704,967,795,819]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">Pempheris rhomboidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(their “ 
<emphasis box="[1056,1198,795,819]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
<taxonomicName box="[1056,1190,795,819]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mangula">P. mangula</taxonomicName>
”
</emphasis>
) from 
<taxonomicName box="[1278,1436,795,819]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis box="[1278,1436,795,819]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. nesogallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by two characters. The first is eye diameter: 13.0– 
<number box="[720,768,829,854]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="15.3">15.3</number>
% SL for “ 
<emphasis box="[892,1033,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
<taxonomicName box="[892,1026,829,853]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mangula">P. mangula</taxonomicName>
”
</emphasis>
and 
<number box="[1089,1201,829,854]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="12.2" valueMax="12.8" valueMin="11.6">11.6–12.8</number>
% for 
<taxonomicName box="[1271,1429,829,853]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis box="[1271,1429,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. nesogallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We invite the reader to measure the eye diameter as a percentage of the SL of the 
<typeStatus box="[1059,1157,864,888]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1193,1349,864,888]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis box="[1193,1349,864,888]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. nesogallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in their 
<figureCitation box="[151,217,898,923]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,2013,2035]" captionTargetBox="[241,1335,1332,1996]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[241,1335,1332,1997]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pempheris nesogallica, BPBM 20144, 117 mm SL, Mauritius (J. E. Randall)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230622/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
Fig. 
<number box="[203,217,898,923]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
A and B. We obtain an eye diameter of 13.0% SL for the fish of their 
<figureCitation box="[1009,1075,898,923]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,2013,2035]" captionTargetBox="[241,1335,1332,1996]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[241,1335,1332,1997]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pempheris nesogallica, BPBM 20144, 117 mm SL, Mauritius (J. E. Randall)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230622/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
Fig. 
<number box="[1061,1075,898,923]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
A, hence barely 
<taxonomicName box="[1266,1429,899,923]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhomboidea">
<emphasis box="[1266,1429,899,923]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. rhomboidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<number box="[198,247,934,958]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="14.1">14.1</number>
% for the fish of their 
<figureCitation box="[497,563,933,958]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,2013,2035]" captionTargetBox="[241,1335,1332,1996]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[241,1335,1332,1997]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pempheris nesogallica, BPBM 20144, 117 mm SL, Mauritius (J. E. Randall)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230622/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
Fig. 
<number box="[549,563,933,958]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
B, thus also 
<taxonomicName box="[708,871,933,957]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhomboidea">
<emphasis box="[708,871,933,957]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. rhomboidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, if we follow 
<bibRefCitation box="[1154,1374,933,958]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" refString="Koeda, K., Yoshino, T., Imai, H. &amp; Tachihara, K. (2014). A review of the genus Pempheris (Perciformes, Pempheridae), with description of a new species. Zootaxa, 3793 (3), 301 - 330. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3793.3.1" type="journal article">
Koeda 
<emphasis box="[1234,1291,933,957]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[1305,1366,934,958]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, both 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,968,992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[289,448,968,992]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis box="[289,448,968,992]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. nesogallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should now be reidentified as 
<emphasis box="[802,974,968,992]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
<taxonomicName box="[802,970,968,992]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhomboidea">P. rhomboidea</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Actually, from our measurements of the eye diameter of all specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[546,707,1003,1027]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis box="[546,707,1003,1027]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. nesogallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[770,936,1003,1027]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhomboidea">
<emphasis box="[770,936,1003,1027]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. rhomboidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
available to us, specifically from the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1003,1027]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">type</typeStatus>
regions, we can find no difference in eye size between these two species (
<figureCitation box="[969,1038,1037,1062]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1980,2002]" captionTargetBox="[266,1326,1184,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[234,1326,1148,1954]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Orbit diameter vs. standard length for specimens of Pempheris nesogallica (open circles) and P. rhomboidea (closed squares)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230620/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
Fig. 
<number box="[1021,1038,1038,1062]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). We repudiate here the designation of MNHN-IC-A-0222 (“ 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" box="[426,516,1072,1096]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">MNHN</collectionCode>
A 
<number box="[544,588,1072,1096]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="222.0">222</number>
” in 
<bibRefCitation author="Koeda" box="[636,849,1071,1096]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" refString="Koeda, K., Yoshino, T., Imai, H. &amp; Tachihara, K. (2014). A review of the genus Pempheris (Perciformes, Pempheridae), with description of a new species. Zootaxa, 3793 (3), 301 - 330. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3793.3.1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Koeda 
<emphasis box="[717,774,1072,1096]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[790,849,1072,1096]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)) as the 
<typeStatus box="[948,1051,1071,1096]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1090,1253,1072,1096]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhomboidea">
<emphasis box="[1090,1253,1072,1096]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. rhomboidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="8" pageNumber="385" refString="Koeda, K., Yoshino, T., Imai, H. &amp; Tachihara, K. (2014). A review of the genus Pempheris (Perciformes, Pempheridae), with description of a new species. Zootaxa, 3793 (3), 301 - 330. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3793.3.1" type="journal article">
Koeda 
<emphasis box="[1379,1436,1072,1096]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[158,217,1107,1131]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
because the basis for their selection is erroneous.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230620/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" targetBox="[266,1326,1184,1938]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1980,2032]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,1980,2002]" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
Orbit diameter vs. standard length for specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[843,1078,1980,2002]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis box="[843,1078,1980,2002]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">
<taxonomicName box="[843,951,1980,2002]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pempheris</taxonomicName>
nesogallica
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(open circles) and 
<taxonomicName box="[1285,1436,1980,2002]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhomboidea">
<emphasis box="[1285,1436,1980,2002]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="385">P. rhomboidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(closed squares).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,558]" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">
Their second character, the presence or absence of stripes is also mistaken. Both species usually have a striped pattern in life from a dark bronze or copper spot on each scale, but can vary from being nearly uniform to having a striped pattern when preserved (
<figureCitation box="[529,611,221,246]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1268,1290]" captionTargetBox="[289,1275,601,1244]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[289,1276,601,1244]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pempheris rhomboidea, BPBM 18425, 123 mm SL, Gulf of Aqaba (J. E. Randall)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230621/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">
Figs. 
<number box="[597,611,221,246]" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[674,690,221,246]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,2013,2035]" captionTargetBox="[241,1335,1332,1996]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[241,1335,1332,1997]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pempheris nesogallica, BPBM 20144, 117 mm SL, Mauritius (J. E. Randall)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230622/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">
<number box="[674,690,221,246]" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). However, we have found a viable morphological character to separate 
<taxonomicName box="[251,508,256,280]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis box="[251,508,256,280]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">Pempheris nesogallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[579,743,256,280]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhomboidea">
<emphasis box="[579,743,256,280]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">P. rhomboidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: the length of the pectoral fin relative to the standard length. This fin is the most durable of the fins of preserved specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[886,1006,291,315]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[886,1006,291,315]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">Pempheris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is measured from the most anterior end of the fin base (the base extends to the edge of the opercular membrane) to the tip of the longest ray. We measured both fins of each fish and used the longest measurement. We have taken pectoral-fin lengths of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">P. nesogallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only from specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[589,698,394,419]" name="Mauritius" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[752,887,394,419]" name="Madagascar" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and of 
<taxonomicName box="[971,1134,395,419]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhomboidea">
<emphasis box="[971,1134,395,419]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">P. rhomboidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only from specimens from the northern Red Sea and the Mediterranean Sea. Nineteen specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[979,1136,429,453]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis box="[979,1136,429,453]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">P. nesogallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<quantity box="[1151,1308,429,454]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0775" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.655" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" unit="mm" value="107.75" valueMax="150.0" valueMin="65.5">65.5–150 mm</quantity>
SL, have a pectoral-fin length of 
<quantity box="[412,544,463,488]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5725" metricValueMax="9.017" metricValueMin="8.128" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" unit="in" value="3.375" valueMax="3.55" valueMin="3.2">3.2–3.55 in</quantity>
SL. By contrast, 
<specimenCount box="[762,919,463,488]" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" type="generic">
<number box="[762,790,464,488]" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" value="12.0">12</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[967,1135,464,488]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhomboidea">
<emphasis box="[967,1135,464,488]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">P. rhomboidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<quantity box="[1154,1294,463,488]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.03" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.76" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" unit="mm" value="103.0" valueMax="130.0" valueMin="76.0">76–130 mm</quantity>
SL, have a pectoral-fin length of 
<quantity box="[398,526,498,523]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6835" metricValueMax="8.128" metricValueMin="7.239" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" unit="in" value="3.025" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="2.85">2.85–3.2 in</quantity>
SL. The two species are very similar in meristic characters. Only the number of anal soft rays shows a difference, 
<number box="[531,601,533,558]" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" value="41.5" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="38.0">38–45</number>
for 
<taxonomicName box="[647,804,533,557]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nesogallica">
<emphasis box="[647,804,533,557]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">P. nesogallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 
<number box="[850,920,533,558]" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" value="38.5" valueMax="41.0" valueMin="36.0">36–41</number>
for 
<taxonomicName box="[966,1129,533,557]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhomboidea">
<emphasis box="[966,1129,533,557]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">P. rhomboidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[1143,1226,533,558]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,239,528,551]" captionText="TABLE 1. Anal Soft Ray Counts of Species of Pempheris from the Western Indian Ocean." pageId="9" pageNumber="386">
Table 
<number box="[1213,1226,534,558]" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" value="1.0">1</number>
</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1114,1268,1290]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230621/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="386" targetBox="[289,1275,601,1244]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1114,1268,1290]" box="[151,1114,1268,1290]" pageId="9" pageNumber="386">
